for this module. I did `pip install crayons` and noticed that it does not have the `normal()` method. Could you push a new version so it includes the latest code?", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/19", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/19/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/19/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/19/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/19", "id": 360784740, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzNjA3ODQ3NDA=", "number": 19, "title": "Does not respect TERM=dumb", "user": {"login": "duck2", "id": 12058255, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDU4MjU1", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/12058255?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2", "html_url": "https://github.com/duck2", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/duck2/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2018-09-17T09:23:05Z", "updated_at": "2019-09-09T09:48:26Z", "closed_at": "2019-09-09T09:48:26Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nI'm using pipenv in an [Acme win](https://research.swtch.com/acme) which doesn't recognize ANSI escape sequences and prints garbled output instead of colors. In other words, it is a dumb terminal and it sets `TERM=dumb` so nobody tries to pass colors to it.\r\n\r\npipenv prints `Usage: \u001b[39m\u001b[1mpipenv\u001b[39m\u001b[22m [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...` which I suppose is actually crayons behavior.\r\n\r\nCrayons already seems to support turning colors off, so I will try to make a PR which implements turning colors off on `TERM=dumb`.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/18", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/18/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/18/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/18/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/18", "id": 359121138, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzNTkxMjExMzg=", "number": 18, "title": "Add function to just make bold text", "user": {"login": "jayanthkoushik", "id": 5206607, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUyMDY2MDc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/5206607?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik", "html_url": "https://github.com/jayanthkoushik", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jayanthkoushik/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-09-11T16:19:03Z", "updated_at": "2019-02-14T13:43:39Z", "closed_at": "2019-02-14T13:43:39Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Sometimes, it's desirable to have bold text without specifying color (to be consistent with different backgrounds). At the moment, it seems like there isn't any way to do this with `crayons`, and a `crayons.bold` function should be easy to add. Another advantage is to allow chaining bold/color calls. For example,\r\n\r\n    if condition_1:\r\n        msg = crayons.red(msg)\r\n    if condition_2:\r\n        msg = crayons.bold(msg)\r\n\r\n It should be a very simple function to add, and I'd be happy to make a pull request.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/16", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/16/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/16/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/16/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/MasterOdin/crayons/issues/16", "id": 358631489, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzNTg2MzE0ODk=", "number": 16, "title": "Blue is too dark on the black background", "user": {"login": "stardust85", "id": 3637559, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM2Mzc1NTk=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/3637559?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/stardust85", "html_url": "https://github.com/stardust85", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stardust85/fol